<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#114)]" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710a-114">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-25">July 25,
                                    1945</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Victory1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi></gloss>
                                316. For Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName>[.]
                                London’s 44360 July 24<note n="2" xml:id="d710a-114fn2"><ref target="#d1031">Document No. 1031</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note> received. <persName corresp="#p_SSW1">Strang</persName> told <persName corresp="#p_MPE1">Mosely</persName> today FonOff has full authority instruct
                                    <persName corresp="#p_HV1">Hood</persName> accept Soviet final
                                paragraph covering report on French zone.<note n="3" xml:id="d710a-114fn3">Cf. the following passage in a personal
                                    letter from <persName corresp="#p_MPE1">Mosely</persName>, dated
                                    at Babelsberg July 24, to <persName corresp="#p_LEAJ1">E. Allan
                                        Lightner, Jr.</persName>, Secretary of the United States
                                    Delegation to the European Advisory Commission (file No.
                                    740.00119 Control (Germany)/7–2445): “<persName corresp="#p_SSW1">Strang</persName> has just told me that
                                    instructions were sent to <persName corresp="#p_HV1">Hood</persName> on July 22 to accept the Soviet formula for
                                    the final sentence of the report. The British agree that the
                                    exact definition of the French sector should be done by military
                                    agreement and need not be incorporated into the <gloss target="#t_EAC1">EAC</gloss> Agreement.”</note> Meanwhile
                                US, <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> and French commanders have
                                agreed on French area in Berlin.<note n="4" xml:id="d710a-114fn4">See <ref target="#d1028">document No. 1028</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SSW1">Strang</persName> obviously does not
                                understand FonOff delay.</p>
                            <p><persName corresp="#p_G10">Gousev</persName> told <persName corresp="#p_MPE1">Mosely</persName> today instructions sent
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SGF1">Saksin</persName> yesterday to
                                accept title of agreement on additional requirements with inclusion
                                of words “to be imposed.”</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_BJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>